AdminChanged(address,address).details: Emitted when the admin account has changed.

BeaconUpgraded(address).details: Emitted when the beacon is changed.

Initialized(uint8).details: Triggered when the contract has been initialized or reinitialized.

Paused(address).details: Emitted when the pause is triggered by `account`.

Unpaused(address).details: Emitted when the pause is lifted by `account`.

Upgraded(address).details: Emitted when the implementation is upgraded.

deposit(address,uint256[],uint256,addres.details: Deposits tokens in the given pool. Creates new Farm contract if there isn't one deployed for the {swap} and deposits tokens in it. Emits a {Deposit} event.

params.minAmountLP: - Minimum LP the user will receive from {amounts} deposit.
params.recipient: - Address which will receive the deposit.

returns.liquidity: - Total liquidity sent to the farm (in lpTokens).

depositETH(address,uint256[],uint256,add.details: Autoconverts ETH into WETH and deposits tokens in the given pool. Creates new Farm contract if there isn't one deployed for the {swap} and deposits tokens in it.

params.minAmountLP: - Minimum LP the user will receive from {amounts} deposit.
params.recipient: - Address which will receive the deposit.

returns.liquidity: - Total liquidity sent to the farm (in lpTokens).

depositLP(address,uint256,address).details: Deposits tokens in the given pool. Creates new Farm contract if there isn't one deployed for the {lpPool} and deposits tokens in it. Emits a {Deposit} event.

params.recipient: - Address which will receive the deposit.
params.swap: - Address of the pool to deposit tokens in.

depositWithSwap(address,bytes[],uint256,.details: Deposits tokens in the given pool with swap. Creates new Farm contract if there isn't one deployed for the {swap}, swaps {token} for pool tokens and deposits them. Emits a {Deposit} event.

params.minAmountLP: - Minimum LP the user will receive from {tokens} deposit.
params.recipient: - Address which will receive the deposit.
params.swap: - Address of the pool to deposit tokens in.
params.swapData: - Parameter with which 1inch router is being called with.

returns.liquidity: - Total liquidity sent to the farm (in lpTokens).
returns.sent: - Total amount amount sent to the farm.

params.feeTo: - Address to collect fees to. Note: This function can only be called by the distributor.
params.rewardSwapInfos: - Arrays of structs with token arrays describing swap routes from reward to tokens in {swap} and minimum amounts of output tokens that must be received for the transaction not to revert.
params.rewarderSwapInfos: - Arrays of structs with token arrays describing swap routes from rewarder to tokens in {swap} and minimum amounts of output tokens that must be received for the transaction not to revert.

paused().details: Returns true if the contract is paused, and false otherwise.

proxiableUUID().details: Implementation of the ERC1822 {proxiableUUID} function. This returns the storage slot used by the implementation. It is used to validate the implementation's compatibility when performing an upgrade. IMPORTANT: A proxy pointing at a proxiable contract should not be considered proxiable itself, because this risks bricking a proxy that upgrades to it, by delegating to itself until out of gas. Thus it is critical that this function revert if invoked through a proxy. This is guaranteed by the `notDelegated` modifier.

params._fee: -New fee to collect from farms. [10^18 == 100%] Note: This function can only be called by ADMIN_ROLE.

totalDeposits(address).details: Returns total amount locked in the pool. Doesn't take pending rewards into account.

upgradeTo(address).details: Upgrade the implementation of the proxy to `newImplementation`. Calls {_authorizeUpgrade}. Emits an {Upgraded} event.

upgradeToAndCall(address,bytes).details: Upgrade the implementation of the proxy to `newImplementation`, and subsequently execute the function call encoded in `data`. Calls {_authorizeUpgrade}. Emits an {Upgraded} event.

userStake(address,address).details: Returns tokens staked by the {_address} for the given {swap}.

params._address: - The address to check stakes for.

withdraw(address,uint256,uint256[],addre.details: Withdraws tokens from the given pool. Emits a {Withdraw} event.

params.amount: - Amounts of LP tokens to withdraw.
params.minAmounts: - Minimum amounts of tokens sent to {recipient}.
params.recipient: - The address which will receive tokens.

returns.amounts: - Token amounts sent to {recipient}, an array of zeros if withdrawLP == false.

withdrawETH(address,uint256,uint256[],ad.details: Autoconverts WETH into ETH and withdraws tokens from the given pool.

params.minAmounts: - Minimum token amounts the user will receive.
params.recipient: - The address which will receive tokens.

withdrawLP(address,uint256,address).details: Withdraws LP tokens from the given pool. Emits a {Withdraw} event.

params.recipient: - The address which will receive tokens.

withdrawWithSwap(address,uint256,bytes[].details: Withdraws single token from the given pool. Emits a {Withdraw} event. Note: If there are any tokens left to be withdrawn after swaps they will be sent to the {{recipient}} in a respective token (not in {token}).

params.recipient: - Address which will receive the deposit.
params.swapData: - Parameters with which 1inch router is being called with.

returns.amounts: - Amounts sent to the {recipient} from swapData.
returns.dust: - Dust amounts sent to the {recipient} left from swaps.
